3. Estimating Energy Decay in a Quantum System

Using the Kulik Formulaâ€™s harmonic decay principles, we model the energy loss of a quantum particle over time.
Example

We calculate energy decay based on a quantum system's harmonic states and track its stabilization over time.

using System;

namespace KulikFormulaExample
{
    class EnergyDecay
    {
        public static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            double initialEnergy = 100.0; // Joules
            double decayFactor = 0.85; // Harmonic decay per time unit
            int timeUnits = 10;

            Console.WriteLine("Energy over time:");
            for (int t = 0; t <= timeUnits; t++)
            {
                double energy = CalculateEnergy(initialEnergy, decayFactor, t);
                Console.WriteLine($"Time {t}: {energy} J");
            }
        }

        private static double CalculateEnergy(double energy, double decayFactor, int time)
        {
            // Harmonic decay modeled using Kulik's approach
            return energy * Math.Pow(decayFactor, time);
        }
    }
}
